HEADWORD: Cochlea
<hw>Coch"le*a</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧k"l⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., a snail, or snail shell, Gr. <grk>kochli`as</grk> a snail, fr.
<grk>ko`chlos</grk> a shellfish with a spiral shell.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>An appendage of the labyrinth of the internal
ear, which is elongated and coiled into a spiral in mammals. See
<er>Ear</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cochlear</ent>⟦br⟧
